en_content:
AGI - At least 10 people were killed in an Israeli bombing of the early morning on the Jaffa school in Gaza City, > which serves as a refuge for Palestinians > saddled because of the war, said the spokesman for civil defense of the enclave Mahmoud Basal on its Telegram channel.
According to Al Jazeera of Qatar, who cites his correspondents on the spot (Israel does not allow the international press to enter Gaza), at least one of the dead was a child.»
Israeli forces often target schools or health centres in Gaza, which during the war have become a refuge for thousands of displaced people, assuming that Hamas militiamen use them to hide and plan attacks.
So far the army has not commented on the attack on Jaffa's school.
More than 51.260 people were killed and 116,000 wounds in Israeli attacks in Gaza since the beginning of the war in October 2023, according to a count of the health authorities of the Strip. Of these, almost 1,900 have died since Israel resumed the offensive on 18 March, > ending the truce in effect from mid-January.
